1
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Once every hundred years, the Star Festival
lights up the skies over the Mushroom Kingdom.

2
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:38,500
- Mario! You made it!
- Wouldn't miss it, Princess.

3
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:43,000
Peach has been waiting all week.
She says a shooting star landed in the castle garden.

4
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:48,000
It's not a star, Mario. It's... alive.
Look, it's glowing.

5
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:24,000
The whole sky just turned dark.
That's not part of the festival, is it?

6
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:29,000
Airships! The castle is under attack!
Everyone, get inside!

7
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:14,000
Mario! Help! The whole castle —
it's being pulled into the sky!

8
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:19,000
Hold on, Peach! I'm coming!
Nobody steals a castle on my watch!

9
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:04,000
He jumped for the chains, brave and stubborn as ever,
and the dark ships swatted him away like a firefly.

10
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:09,000
And the little star from the garden
followed him down through the cold and the dark.

11
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:04,000
Wake up. Wake up, mister mustache.
You fell a very long way.

12
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:09,000
Where... where am I? The castle!
Peach! Where is she?

13
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:14,000
Far away. Very far. But you're lucky —
I'm a Luma, and Lumas know the way between stars.

14
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:19,000
A talking star. Sure. Why not.
Okay, little guy. Take me to her.

15
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:24,000
First you need power. Star power.
Catch the sparkles, grow the wings. Watch!

16
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:04,000
Whoa! I'm flying! Luigi is never
going to believe this!

17
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:04,000
This is the Comet Observatory.
It sails wherever the comets sail.

18
00:30:05,000 --> 00:30:09,000
And this is Rosalina.
She watches over all of us.

19
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:14,000
Welcome, Mario. The Lumas told me about you.
You're searching for someone you love.

20
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:19,000
Someone took her. Ships out of a black sky.
I don't even know who.

21
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:24,000
I do. And I'm sorry.
Because it means he's found the Grand Stars again.

22
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:29,000
Rosalina, the observatory's engines are cold.
Without the Grand Stars we drift like driftwood.

23
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:04,000
Then we make a deal. I bring back your Grand Stars,
and you sail me to wherever Peach is.

24
00:45:00,000 --> 00:45:04,000
So the plumber survived the fall.
GWAHAHA! Good. I wanted an audience.

25
00:45:05,000 --> 00:45:09,000
Bowser. I should have known.
Where is she, you overgrown turtle?

26
00:45:10,000 --> 00:45:14,000
Somewhere above your head, little man.
I'm done stealing kingdoms. I'm building my own.

27
00:45:15,000 --> 00:45:19,000
A galaxy of my very own, powered by the Grand Stars,
with a throne at the center of everything.

28
00:45:20,000 --> 00:45:24,000
And your princess gets the best seat in the house —
right next to the reactor.

29
00:46:00,000 --> 00:46:04,000
You can still stop this, Bowser.
Give back the stars. Let her go.

30
00:46:05,000 --> 00:46:09,000
Stop? I'm just getting started.
Kamek! Show our guest the exit.

31
01:00:00,000 --> 01:00:04,000
Three Grand Stars, back in their cradles.
The observatory hums like it's young again.

32
01:00:05,000 --> 01:00:09,000
You've done more than I hoped, Mario.
But the last star burns at the heart of his fortress sun.

33
01:00:10,000 --> 01:00:14,000
Then that's where we sail.
All engines, straight into the fire.

34
01:00:15,000 --> 01:00:19,000
There's something you should know first.
About why Bowser's new galaxy can never hold.

35
01:00:20,000 --> 01:00:24,000
A galaxy built on stolen stars collapses inward.
He isn't building a kingdom. He's building a black hole.

36
01:15:00,000 --> 01:15:04,000
Mario! You came! You actually
flew across the universe!

37
01:15:05,000 --> 01:15:09,000
Told you. Nobody steals a castle on my watch.
Now let's get you out of here.

38
01:15:10,000 --> 01:15:14,000
It's too late, look! The fortress sun —
it's folding in on itself!

39
01:20:00,000 --> 01:20:04,000
No! My galaxy! MY GALAXY!
What's happening to my galaxy?!

40
01:20:05,000 --> 01:20:09,000
It was never going to hold, Bowser.
Rosalina tried to warn you. Take my hand!

41
01:20:10,000 --> 01:20:14,000
You'd save ME? After everything?
...You really are the strangest little man.

42
01:21:00,000 --> 01:21:04,000
The little Luma — he's flying into the core!
What is he doing?!

43
01:21:05,000 --> 01:21:09,000
What Lumas are born to do, Mario.
When a star grows up, it becomes a galaxy.

44
01:22:00,000 --> 01:22:05,000
The dark closed like a mouth, and then —
light. A brand new spiral of stars where the hole had been.

45
01:28:00,000 --> 01:28:04,000
The festival's back on. Luigi saved you a seat.
And look — the new galaxy is right overhead.

46
01:28:05,000 --> 01:28:09,000
He's up there somewhere, isn't he? The little guy.
Shining away.

47
01:28:10,000 --> 01:28:14,000
They always come back, Mario.
Stars never really go out.

